      <h2 class="mb-6">What’s to Like About Codebase?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong class="t-text-alt">Easy to start.</strong> Codebase can be <a href="{{ '/docs/1-getting-started/simple-html-setup' | url }}">dropped into your project</a> as-is. No installation. No config file.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="t-text-alt">Easy to learn.</strong> These <a href="{{ '/docs/1-getting-started/simple-html-setup/' | url }}">docs</a> will give you a good idea of what Codebase can do, and how easy it is to use. There are a lot of similarities between Bootstrap and Tailwind – so, if you are familiar with them, you’ll feel at home here.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="my-6">
      <p class="t-center">
